The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Lanka win 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Lanka win 
                      
	Lauderhill (US): Sri Lanka beat New Zealand by seven wickets, with more than four overs to spare, in a low-scoring Twenty20 International in Florida on Sunday where the Black Caps could do no better than 81 all out in 17.3 overs after Nuwan Kulasekeras three wickets for four runs.         
	The tied two-match series was the first time that two Test-playing nations had met in an official game in the United States.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
